The paper deals with the problem of secrecy capacity in wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) and multiple-antenna-eavesdropper (MIMOME) systems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of quantized channel state information (CSI) and feedback bits suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the network information theory (cs.NI) sub-category.
